The '''Galactic Alliance Department of Justice''', also referred to as the '''Ministry of Justice''', was a branch of the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]]. It was formed as a organization of the Galactic Alliance to replace its predecessor, the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[Ministry of Justice (New Republic)|Ministry of Justice]]. The Justice Department was in charge of prosecuting cases and [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|enforcing]] law and order. It also operated the [[Alliance Marshal]]s who conducted investigations for the Department and performed other tasks as needed including escorting [[Prison/Legends|prisoners]] to and from court.

==History==
The [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] Department of Justice was formed in [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]] from its [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[Ministry of Justice (New Republic)|predecessor]].<ref name="DestinyWay" />

After the [[Solo-Niathal coup]], the Justice Department handled the government's prosecution of the deposed [[Chief of State (Galactic Alliance)|Chief of State]] [[Cal Omas]]. However, Omas and his attorneys complained due to the fact that the Department did not charge him with anything until an extended period following his arrest.<ref name="cswe">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref> The matter never went to trial as Omas later killed himself.<ref name="lotf6">''[[Legacy of the Force: Inferno]]''</ref>

In the aftermath of the [[Second Galactic Civil War]], [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] was charged with dereliction of duty for allowing [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] to fall to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]] and take over the Alliance. The [[The Galactic Federation of Free Alliances versus Luke Skywalker|trial]] ended in a 10 year exile for Skywalker unless he could find the reason Jacen fell to the dark side.<ref name="Outcast">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Outcast]]''</ref>

As the relationship between Chief of State [[Natasi Daala]] and the [[New Jedi Order|Jedi Order]] deteroriated, the Chief of State and was able to have Jedi shadowded. The [[Alliance Marshal]]s were assigned as [[Jedi supervisor]]s to make sure that [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] obeyed Galactic Alliance law.<ref name="Outcast" />

The Justice Department pursued a [[Trial of Tahiri Veila|criminal case]] against former Jedi, [[Sith/Legends|Sith]], and [[Galactic Alliance Guard]] [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Tahiri Veila]] for the murder of [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Gilad Pellaeon/Legends|Gilad Pellaeon]].<ref name="Abyss">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Abyss]]''</ref>

Later, the Justice Department ordered [[Trinnolt Makken]] to investigate the death of Acting Grand Master [[Kenth Hamner]]. Hamner had been [[Skirmish in the Operations Hangar|killed]] in a [[Lightsaber duel/Legends|lightsaber duel]] by fellow [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Saba Sebatyne]]. However, the Justice Department was unsure if a death during a lightsaber duel could be considered a crime to charge Master Sebatyne with.<ref name="Conviction">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Conviction]]''</ref>

